<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-19T22:13:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-19T22:13:00-05:00" n="748" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861a.01/344: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winslow</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-20T12:00:00+08:47"><hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                        1922—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received, September 20—5:52
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. Embassy informed. Japanese evacuation zone 1 completed September
                            18th. General Tachibana<note n="75" xml:id="d748fn75">Gen. Koichiro
                                Tachibana, in command of Japanese forces in Siberia.</note> declares
                            that evacuation zone 2 begins today. It is now technically possible for
                            Chita troops to enter Nikolsk.</p>
                        <p>Steamer <hi rend="italic">Tomsk</hi> left here yesterday for Okhotsk
                            carrying reenforcements for White General Pepelaieff<note n="76" xml:id="d748fn76">Gen. Anatoli Nikolaevich Pepelyaev.</note> now
                            operating with outlaw Blokhareff there.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Winslow</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>